The Bundesbank set a new tender for a28-day securities repurchase agreement, offering banksliquidity aid at a fixed bid rate of 3.80 pct, a central bankspokesman said.    Banks must make their bids by 1400 GMT today. Funds will beallocated by 0900 GMT tomorrow and credited to accounts laterin the day. Banks must repurchase securities pledged on May 6. REUTER&#3;